Unless you are planing for 500+ Mrp, you'll generally find skalds going IP+purge or IP+assortment of cheaper RA's, usually MCL, tireless, AoM, MoPain.<br>
Serenity is not bad, but a bad return on investment (it is costly and you need the points for IP, remember). I'd go for MCL1, much more benefits for the cost. Again, serenity is good, I loved it (did like most melees do, took and tried various RA's until i got enough rp for IP and /respecced), but you need the points elsewhere.<br>
Regeneration is nowhere near enough for the cost. Don't waste points on that ability imho.<br>
<br>
<br>
My advice : &quot;pure kite skald&quot; do not exist. Not in the same way as &quot;pure fire wizard&quot;, &quot;pure mana enchanters&quot; or &quot;pure spear heroes&quot; exist. Kiting is an extremely unreliable way to fight. Kiting works, in some circumstances, however don't believe the hype. Kiting was uber 6 months ago and still kick ass in the battlgrounds, but that's it. I am not saying it is useless in real RvR at level 50, but you shouldn't base your template entirely on that.<br>
<br>
You are right on with resists. Myself, I took Avoidance of magic I without hesitation, and may well take a second level later in my career. <br>
<br>
I am concerned about your spec choice if you want to kite however. Kiting relies heavily on your shout damage. Going with the template 50 weapon/43BS will significantly reduce your DD output, thus jeopardizing your kiting attempt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=seneckkaul>seneckkaul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/15/02 6:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ahh</span><hr size=1> well i must say. after looking at my post i guess i wanna do kind of both: Kite and Melee. So not being pure Kite allows me to be supporting the group by charging when the enemy is weak( or if i think so then he turns into a moose, or even worse his wounds miraculously heal..DOH!!).<br>
