<br>
Other RA's to get would be Purge, IP/FA2, Mastery of Pain, Mastery of Parrying, Augmented Str/Con, Toughness, Long Wind 1 (this gives you perma sprint when combined with Shaman End 4), Avoidance of Magic.<br>
<br>
Generally, unless you have *a lot* of RP's, you don't want to take any RA to the 4th teir (Avoidance of Magic 4 for example) because the return on the points invested at that point has decreased a lot from when you first started buying it, that it is practically useless.<br>
<br>
As for your template, 50 Axe / 43 Song is good. If you plan on kiting only, you really don't need 50 Axe, since you won't be relying on melee so much, but you will want the last DD at 46 songs. To get that, you could drop to 44 Axe and put some points into Parry, just for safe keeping. One point in parry gives you an added .5% chance to parry. With a low spec of 17 parry, you will not spend a lot of points but you will still get 9% chance to parry (more with +parry item bonuses).<br>
<br>
This is my plan: 46 Songs, 44 Axe, 17 Parry<br>
<br>
RA's: Ignore Pain, First Aid 2, Aug Dex 2, Mastery of Pain 2, MCL 1<br>
<br>
Then I'll work on things like Aug Con, Toughness, Avoidance of Magic, Mastery of Parrying, Aug Str, Lifter 1, Long Wind 1<br>
<br>
